<refnamediv>
<refname>Client Stream</refname>
<refpurpose>Create a GskStream which is connecting to a remote address.</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv id="gsk-gskstreamclient.synopsis" role="synopsis">
<title role="synopsis.title">Synopsis</title>

<synopsis>
<link linkend="GskStream">GskStream</link> *         <link linkend="gsk-stream-new-connecting">gsk_stream_new_connecting</link>           (<link linkend="GskSocketAddress">GskSocketAddress</link> *address,
                                                         <link linkend="GError">GError</link> **error);
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>









<refsect1 id="gsk-gskstreamclient.description" role="desc">
<title role="desc.title">Description</title>
<para>
A simple method to create a GskStream which is connecting
to a remote address, without any of the low-level hassles.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="gsk-gskstreamclient.details" role="details">
<title role="details.title">Details</title>
<refsect2 id="gsk-stream-new-connecting" role="function">
<title>gsk_stream_new_connecting ()</title>
<indexterm zone="gsk-stream-new-connecting"><primary sortas="gsk_stream_new_connecting">gsk_stream_new_connecting</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="GskStream">GskStream</link> *         gsk_stream_new_connecting           (<link linkend="GskSocketAddress">GskSocketAddress</link> *address,
                                                         <link linkend="GError">GError</link> **error);</programlisting>
<para>
Create a stream connecting to a given address.</para>
<para>
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>address</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> the address to connect to.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><parameter>error</parameter>&#160;:</term>
<listitem><simpara> optional place to put an error response.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term><listitem><simpara> the newly created stream.
</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2>

</refsect1>




